I really have nothing to report.  My life has become nothing but about food, sleep, and entertainment.  Sounds nice and it is for the most part, but there is little challenge.  I'm the kind of girl who likes to work.  I'm the nerd who can't wait to go back to school.  One more month of loafing for me and then it's tome to buckle down and act the like the adult I supposedly am.

Today I made french bread pizza with Ja'ames for his family, then played his gameboy, Tetris.  WHO DOESN'T LOVE TETRIS!?!?  Then I came home to watch "Sex and the City" reruns on TBS with my sister.

I know, I know . . . I live a most exciting life.

I've been watching a lot of movies lately, or so it seems.

All are good movies.  "DodgeBall" sticks out from the rest . . . it's a great movie for a laugh, but the others are pretty depressing, but great.

I saw this movie with James on Thursday.  Before we watched the movie, I got a large popcorn and a Mr. Pibb.  While this movie made me want to eat healthier, I have no problem scarfing down my movie treats.  Extra butter . . . yes please!

Today was a great day spent with Ja'ames.  We cooked dinner for his family, a new Tuesday night affair.  We made french dip sandwiches, black cherry sweet tea, salad, and lemon pound cake with strawberries.  Very tasty.  Then we took a walk, and did some good old fashion watching of the boob tube.  At 11:00pm, we caught the season finally of "The Sopranos."

My Mom seems to be doing well too with these divorce proceedings.  I am glad.

SMILE.

Whelp today I said goodbye to my uncle and aunt, after a nice parting trip to the liquor store and lunch out.  I got a nice bottle of melon flavored vodka, can't wait for future cape coders.  I spent the rest of the day fixing all the photos I have taken in the last few weeks.  I now have cable in my room too, hiding all kinds of cables from the living room to my bedroom.  I KNOW, EXCITING STUFF.

I graduated a few weeks ago.  That was a long, hot, and boring event, but at least I won't regret not going later.  I think I was too hungry to enjoy most of it and most of my art friends are on the five-year VCU plan instead of the four, so I knew few grads.  I was glad to leave Richmond, go home, and put of a pair of shorts and a t-shirt.

 

The only good thing about graduation so far is getting to see people you don't get to see all the time, like family and friends.  Though, after a while, you just want to be alone and not have to worry about entertaining.  It's been a non-stop parade of people since graduation weekend. 

 

The past few weeks I have been without internet, except checking briefly at Ja'ames once a week.  Now I am finally online.  I didn't really miss it.  Funny thing happened when with the installation.  Cable guy Dan decided to call my phone around 9:30pm to ask us how our internet was working out.  I said "fine?!#?".  And then there was a long pause from him and I said "is that all?"  Then he proceeded to ask if my sister Carrie would like to go out on a date with him and I quickly replied that she was engaged.  It was very creepy and funny all at the same time.  Everyone, my family and James, were in the middle of a game of pictionary, so I decided to draw an ape-like Dan the Cable Man grabbing on to Carrie's as a talk bubble came out of his mouth that said "PREMIUM!" when it was my turn.  Premium as is premium cable or premium as in Carrie's pretty hot.  We all agreed later that maybe if he really wanted a chance with her, he should have upgraded our cable, not downgraded us.

 

Gardenias are in bloom and that makes me pretty glad.  They smell so nice.  Random but true.

 

I went to the beach today with my family, included my aunt and uncle who are visiting.  I swam in the ocean for the first time this year. It was pretty salty but felt so nice.  I walk along the boardwalk to dry in just my bathing suit with little self-consciousness.  Usually this would not be the case.  I was proud of myself.

 

So much is new, I'm just trying to think of it all.

 

James decided to dye his hair bright crayola red.  I forget he's done it all the time, so when he comes over, I say "OH YEAH!"

I bought new bedroom furniture.  I've been struggling to find time to fix my room up with all our guests, but it is shaping up.

Ja'ames got me the new "Sex and the City" DVD, season six, part 1.  I watched it already with my sister.  I love that show.

My mom has a hearing Wednesday dealing with her divorce from my Dad.  That's a downer.  I hope the outcome is in her favor.

Life's pretty okay lately.  Tonight I will eat meatloaf for dinner and it will be great.  It's great being home.  I miss my school buddies.

Hope everyone is doing great.  Drop me a line.

Hmm, just went to me last exam/class at VCU.  I am not sure if this makes me sad or happy.  I think probably both at the same time.  I am glad to be moving back home, but I am going to miss all the friends I have made and the good times.  I guess the line "When I grow up . . ." doesn't apply to me anymore.  I'll really be living it soon.  It's new and exciting, just a hard adjustment.  I'm scared.  But that's what I love about life, new experiences.  I'll never stop learning.  Maybe now that I'm not in art school anymore, I'll start to enjoy making art again.

Who knows.  I don't want to think hard for the next week at least.

I have not done much with the live journal is a few weeks, except for those addicting quizzes.  I think I've just been so busy.  Graduation is just around the corner, and I have been busy making plans.  It looks like I'll be able to have one last summer of minimal responsibilities, aka no job.  I've been saving away, and plan to get a nice tax return and money back from VCU, because I am moving out of my dorm early.  I plan to take trips and see family and swim till this extra weight melts away.  Being a Student Manager is not as physically demanding as my old position and it shows.

 

In August though, I'll have to buckle down, get a job, and work on the steps needed to become an art teacher.  Number one lately seems to be though helping out my Mom, who is going through a difficult time.  Since her separation from my Dad, she's been working two jobs and recently as move out on her with no support from my dad.  She's been barely making it and from time to time has had to rely on my sister and I . . . which I see as very unfair, but I would do anything for her.  Actually she quit her second job last week, because it was putting too much strain on her.  Anyway, to make a long story short, I can't wait to move back in with her, pull my own weight help out anyway I can.

 

I just took my last test as an undergraduate.  It's not as exciting as it seems.  I still have three more critiques to look forward to.  One project is an animation which I have only half way completed . . . bad Colleen.  I will get it done though.  I always do.  I am just too excited to be moving away from Richmond.  Of coarse there will be people and places to miss, but my mind has always been half not here with my family and James so far away.  Seeing Ja'ames on a regular basic will be extra nice.

 

Okay, so I am promising myself to write here more often that I have been so I can keep up with people or vice versa.

 

Bye live journal.

well, i got my cap and gown for graduation today . . . i can't wait until i get to wear it, even though it is really just an ugly black moo-moo with sleeves. my sash for the school of the arts is brown . . . brown? . . . you'd think BFA graduates would get to wear a more vibrate color than brown . . . or maybe they give the art students brown because only we can truly appreciate the color most people associate with poop, mud, and chocolate milk . . . moooooo . . .

i'm kinda depressed to be back at school, even if it is just for 2 more months.  all i really want to do is go back home.  home, that's where i went for my spring break.  no beaches and sun for me.  spring break fell in just the right place this year.  i got a whole nine days away from cold and ugly richmond, where I celebrated my 22nd birthday with my family and friends and my anniversary with ja'ames.  this year's was a pleasant change to previous anniversaries with ja'ames.  one comes to mind, where we both had to go to class and work all day.  the only time we got to spend with each other was sitting on my floor with our backs against the couch in my living room with out legs under the coffee table for an hour while we split a ham sandwich and a orange I brought home from the dinning hall.  this year, we got to go out to a nice dinner and a movie, which may sound lame, but it's rare we get to just go to dinner and a movie.  one regrete though was the movie we saw.  why james and i thought it would be a good idea to see a movie about a female serial killer, "monster," on our anniversary, i don't know.  now, when i go to bed at night, sometimes when i wake up, and sometimes when i have nothing better to think about, i think about one scene in particular that involves charlize theron, a lead pipe, and a gallon of rubbing alcohol.  "monster" is my new "boys don't cry," a really good movie i will never watch again.  and, well, the rest of the week, before and after my monster thoughts, was pretty great too.  i spent lots of time with my mom for a change.  usually, she's at work at one of her two jobs.  i repotted my aloe vera plant, douglas, who is becoming quit a big boy these days and I baked my first carrot cake.  maybe i am a big old dork now, but i just love those times when I finally get to do something besides go to school or work.  speaking of school and work, i should be getting to bed.  it's back to the grind stone.  all that is left of my break is happy memories and the dozen roses james gave me.  i'm not a sappy romantic, but I do like flowers every now and then.  neither of us itch yet, the seven year itch.  good times, noodle salad.

goodnight.

the phrase "if i had a hammer, i'd hit you in the head" has been stuck in my head for the last several weeks.  i don't know why this is, it just is.

on friday i will be 22 and it will be my spring break.  i am looking forward to seeing my mom and spending time with james.  we have an anniversary on march 19, seven years.  i have known ja'ames for more than a third of my life, which is pretty amazing. 

so seven years, everyone asks . . . are we going to get married . . . i don't know . . . will james buy me jewelry . . . i don't know . . . all i know is, i'm having a good time in the now and for me that is good enough . . .
